TRexSelector — Changelog
========================

Version 0.1.0 — 2026-05-11
---------------------------

First installable release of the C++ TRexSelector library.

Package infrastructure
  - cmake --install now produces a fully relocatable install tree:
    include/   (63 public headers, no demo headers)
    lib/       (static libraries for all four targets)
    lib/cmake/TRexSelector/   (TRexSelectorConfig.cmake,
                               TRexSelectorConfigVersion.cmake,
                               TRexSelectorTargets.cmake)
  - Downstream projects can now use:
      find_package(TRexSelector REQUIRED)
      target_link_libraries(myapp PRIVATE TRexSelector::trex_selector_methods)

CMake changes
  - Added TREX_BUILD_DEMOS option (default ON); gates Matplot++ and demo
    executables so library-only builds do not require a plotting library
  - All four library targets declare FILE_SET HEADERS for correct header
    installation and IDE indexing
  - Single authoritative install(EXPORT TRexSelectorTargets) in root
    CMakeLists.txt; duplicate removed from tsolvers
  - Blanket install(DIRECTORY src/) removed; replaced by FILE_SET rules
  - CMakePresets.json: added release-libs configure preset (TREX_BUILD_DEMOS=OFF),
    release-build-libs build preset, release-libs workflow preset,
    vcpkg-release configure/build/workflow presets

CPack packaging
  - cmake --build <dir> --target package produces
    TRexSelector-<version>-<system>.tar.gz and .zip (binary archive)
  - cmake --build <dir> --target package_source produces
    TRexSelector-<version>-src.tar.gz and .zip (source archive);
    excludes build/, install/, simulations/, R/, Python/, notes/, tests/

vcpkg dependency manifest
  - vcpkg.json at repo root declares eigen3, boost-headers, boost-iostreams,
    cereal, and libomp (macOS only) as managed dependencies
  - cmake --workflow --preset vcpkg-release auto-installs all dependencies
    via vcpkg before building

